main event: On December 24, 1953, two U.S. Navy pilots sighted ten unidentified flying objects over El Cajon, California.
interesting points: The objects were observed for five minutes flying in a straight line,The objects were oval, silvery in color and of unknown size,The speed of the objects was reported to be greater than 400 knots with no visible propulsion,The pilots had over 24 years of flying experience,No other reports or interceptions were made despite air traffic in the area.
witness description: U.S. Navy pilots from V-122, USNAS Miramar
